Week 5-6: Build Dashboard & Deploy
Goals: Create professional Power BI dashboard
Dashboard Components:
Page 1: Overview

Map of Calgary with hotspots highlighted (heatmap)
Total crimes by type (bar chart)
Trend over time (line chart)
Key metrics: total crimes, % change, high-risk zones

Page 2: Predictions

Next week's predicted hotspots (map)
Crime type predictions by zone
Recommended patrol allocation
Confidence levels for predictions

Page 3: Resource Allocation

Optimize patrol routes based on predictions
Show: current vs. recommended deployment
Calculate: potential crimes prevented

Tasks:

Integrate Python + Power BI

Use Python visuals in Power BI OR
Export predictions to CSV, import to Power BI


Create DAX Measures

Example: Crime Rate = DIVIDE([Total Crimes], [Population])
Calculate KPIs: % change, averages, rankings


Design Professional Dashboard

Use police-appropriate colors (blues, professional)
Clear labels and legends
Interactive filters (date range, crime type, district)


Add Interactivity

Click neighborhood → see details
Adjust date → predictions update
Filter by crime type



Deliverable: Interactive Power BI dashboard (.pbix file)